Ensures a single instance. Often overused; prefer DI. If used, make it lazy, thread-safe, and testable.

Python:
class Singleton: _inst=None
 def __new__(cls,*a,**k):
 if not cls._inst: cls._inst=super().__new__(cls)
 return cls._inst

Java:
enum Singleton { INSTANCE }

C++:
T& instance(){ static T inst; return inst; }
